        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 19 1874</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I beg leave to thank you very sincerely for your kindness in having sent me your memoir on Climbing Plants which I shall be extremely glad to read soon.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>With my best thanks &amp; respect I remain | dear Sir | yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">There are annotated offprints of Vries’s two articles on climbing plants (Vries 1873a and 1873b) in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL. CD cited them frequently in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1458.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Climbing plants</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, published in 1875.</note>
        </div>        
            
